00:18:04.270 --> 00:18:06.500
RETO MEIER: Hey, Alex.

00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:13.880
ALEX: This project started in
2007 on Symbian when Android

00:18:13.880 --> 00:18:16.090
was just in its infancy.

00:18:16.090 --> 00:18:19.660
So the idea back then was to
track my motorcycle tour

00:18:19.660 --> 00:18:20.710
around Europe.

00:18:20.710 --> 00:18:25.060
I wanted to show my friends back
home where I was, where

00:18:25.060 --> 00:18:26.820
my friend was at well.

00:18:26.820 --> 00:18:27.740
So I made the app.

00:18:27.740 --> 00:18:29.780
It had no login, no nothing.

00:18:29.780 --> 00:18:30.710
It just showed--

00:18:30.710 --> 00:18:32.730
there was just a website, and
you could just see where this

00:18:32.730 --> 00:18:35.500
one Nokia phone was.

00:18:35.500 --> 00:18:39.700
In those days, GPS on phones
was completely new.

00:18:39.700 --> 00:18:42.545
So quite late, actually, last
year, I released this Android

00:18:42.545 --> 00:18:48.665
version, which represents
about 120 hours of work.

00:18:48.665 --> 00:18:50.815
It has all the same features
in it that

00:18:50.815 --> 00:18:52.940
the Symbian one did.

00:18:52.940 --> 00:18:55.830
Which it kind to morphed into a
security product long before

00:18:55.830 --> 00:18:59.230
it was built into your iPhone
or Android device.

00:18:59.230 --> 00:19:04.010
