you can find the phone.

00:19:11.370 --> 00:19:16.420
[ALARM]

00:19:16.420 --> 00:19:18.860
ALEX: So it creates
a notification.

00:19:18.860 --> 00:19:20.950
You have to deactivate
the notification.

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:23.520
You can choose whether or not
you want to hide that message

00:19:23.520 --> 00:19:28.470
so that the person who has the
phone can see it or not.

00:19:28.470 --> 00:19:32.060
You can set a passcode as well
so that the person who has the

00:19:32.060 --> 00:19:34.180
phone has to type in a passcode
before they can

00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:36.720
disable the alarm.

00:19:36.720 --> 00:19:38.560
It has a bugging message
feature.

00:19:38.560 --> 00:19:42.220
So if the SIM card on the phone
is changed, it will text

00:19:42.220 --> 00:19:47.060
a pre-defined number saying,
this is the new number that's

00:19:47.060 --> 00:19:48.730
in the telephone.

